# Job Digest — 2026-03-22

Track: core_crypto
Run timestamp: 2026-03-22 09:59:00 CET
Sources checked: 15
New roles found: 3
High-signal matches: 2

## Executive summary

Found 3 new roles worth noting. Two older IACR-listed positions still appear live and are technically strong matches, but both are outside Jonas's preferred locations and need a quick status check because they were posted in late 2025. One Germany-based secunet role is a plausible borderline option if he wants to broaden into mobile secure-communications engineering.

## Recommended actions

- Check whether the NTU `FHE Engineer` role is still actively hiring; it is the closest technical match in this pass but the stated January/February 2026 start makes timing uncertain.
- Check whether the Monash `Post-Doc on Blockchain` role is still open; it is a strong research fit, but it is an academic relocation to Melbourne.
- Watch the secunet `Software Developer mobile (m/w/d) VPN und Security (Android/iOS)` role only if Jonas wants to lean into product-facing secure mobile/VPN engineering.

## Strong matches

### 1. FHE Engineer — TT-logic / Nanyang Technological University
Link: https://syllab-ntu.github.io/syllab/2026_FHE_engineer/
Location: NTU, Singapore
Remote: onsite
Team / domain: privacy-preserving inference / FHE
Posted: 2025-11-21
Source: IACR Jobs

Why it matches:
- Direct responsibility for implementing and optimizing FHE-based privacy-preserving inference, with explicit use of Zama Concrete-ML and other FHE libraries.
- Strong overlap with Jonas's background in applied cryptography, privacy-preserving systems, and research-to-engineering translation.
- The role sits at the research-engineering boundary rather than generic software work.

Possible concerns:
- The stated start date is January/February 2026, so as of March 22, 2026 the hiring timeline is uncertain even though the page says applications are accepted until the position is filled.
- Singapore onsite and fixed-term (12/18 months, extendable).

Fit score: 8/10
Recommendation: watch

### 2. Post-Doc on Blockchain — Monash University
Link: https://iacr.org/news/item/27284
Location: Melbourne, Australia
Remote: unknown
Team / domain: blockchain privacy and security / quantum-safe solutions
Posted: 2025-12-14
Source: IACR Jobs

Why it matches:
- The work is explicitly on privacy-preserving blockchain systems, Layer 2/off-chain transactions, and quantum-resistant blockchain privacy mechanisms.
- The posting asks for a PhD in cryptography or a closely related area and strong applied/theoretical cryptography depth.
- This is a research-heavy applied cryptography role rather than generic blockchain engineering.

Possible concerns:
- Academic postdoc and Melbourne relocation make it a materially bigger practical commitment.
- Strong preference for prior blockchain-specific cryptography work and a top-tier publication record.

Fit score: 7/10
Recommendation: watch

## Borderline / maybe

### 3. Software Developer mobile (m/w/d) VPN und Security (Android/iOS) — secunet Security Networks AG
Link: https://jobs.secunet.com/Software-Developer-mobile-mwd-VPN-und-Security-AndroidiOS-de-j3208.html
Location: Berlin, Essen or München
Remote: flexible/hybrid; up to 20 days remote within the EU per year
Team / domain: secure mobile communications / VPN
Posted: unknown
Source: secunet jobs

Why it matches:
- The work touches VPN technologies, encryption, authentication, secure storage, and TLS/SSL in a high-security environment.
- Berlin and Munich are directly within Jonas's preferred location set.
- It is one of the cleaner security-engineering fits among the new non-duplicate secunet roles.

Possible concerns:
- The role is much more mobile product engineering than core cryptography, PETs, or research engineering.
- It expects established Android and iOS implementation experience, including `VpnService` / `NetworkExtension` and enterprise deployment concerns.

Fit score: 6/10
Recommendation: watch

